clinical_study.brief_title: An Extension Study to Evaluate the Long-Term Safety and Tolerability of Ubrogepant in the Treatment of Migraine
clinical_study.official_title: A Multicenter, Randomized, Open-Label Extension Study to Evaluate the Long-Term Safety and Tolerability of Oral Ubrogepant in the Acute Treatment of Migraine With or Without Aura

brief_summary.textblock: This study will evaluate the long-term safety and tolerability of intermittent treatment with ubrogepant for the acute treatment of migraine over 1 year.

detailed_description.textblock: Usual care is the open-label control arm. Dose of ubrogepant (50 mg or 100 mg) will be double-blind for active treatment arms.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants With at Least 1 Treatment Emergent Adverse Event
primary_outcome.description: An adverse event (AE) is any untoward medical occurrence in a patient or clinical investigation participant administered a pharmaceutical product and that does not necessarily have a causal relationship with this treatment. An AE can therefore be any unfavorable and unintended sign (including an abnormal laboratory finding), symptom, or disease temporally associated with the use of a medicinal (investigational) product, whether or not related to the medicinal (investigational) product. TEAEs are AEs with an onset that occurs after receiving study drug.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Clinically Significant Laboratory Values
secondary_outcome.description: Hematology, Chemistry and Urinalysis results considered potentially clinically significant (PCS) meeting either the lower-limit or higher-limit PCS criteria.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Clinically Significant Electrocardiograms (ECGs) Findings
secondary_outcome.description: ECG findings considered potentially clinically significant (PCS) meeting either the lower-limit or higher-limit PCS criteria.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Clinically Significant Vital Sign Measurements
secondary_outcome.description: Vital sign measurements considered potentially clinically significant (PCS) meeting either the lower-limit or higher-limit PCS criteria.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants Experiencing Suicidal Ideation or Suicidal Behavior Based on Columbia-Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS) Using 5-Point Scales
secondary_outcome.description: On the C-SSRS, the 5 types of suicidal ideation are: Type 1: "Wish to be dead" Type 2: Non-specific active suicidal thoughts Type 3: "Active suicidal ideation with any methods (not plan) without intent to act" Type 4: "Active suicidal ideation with some intent to act, without specific plan" Type 5: "Active suicidal ideation with specific plan and intent"

arm_group.description: Usual Care as prescribed by the physician as standard of care in clinical practice for the treatment of migraine attacks for up to 1 year.

Ubrogepant 50 mg tablet orally plus placebo-matching ubrogepant tablet for the treatment of a qualifying migraine attack for up to 8 treatments every 4 weeks for up to 1 year. Participants may choose to take a second dose orally after the initial dose if migraine continues or returns.

Ubrogepant 100 mg (two 50 mg tablets) orally for the treatment of a qualifying migraine attack for up to 8 treatments every 4 weeks for up to 1 year. Participants may choose to take a second dose orally after the initial dose if migraine continues or returns.

intervention.description: Ubrogepant tablet(s) orally for the treatment of a qualifying migraine attack.
Ubrogepant placebo-matching tablet orally for the treatment of a qualifying migraine attack.
Treatment for a migraine as prescribed by the physician as standard of care in clinical practice.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
-Completed study UBR-MD-01(NCT02828020) or UBR-MD-02(NCT02867709).
Exclusion Criteria:
- Patients with clinically significant electrocardiogram (ECG), vital sign, physical exam, or laboratory abnormalities
- Requirement for a medication during the study that is on the list of prohibited medications.
